'''拱'''為常見[[建築|建築]]结构之一，型態定義為中央上半成圓弧曲線。拱早期經常運用於跨逕大的橋樑或門首。又可分為箱形拱、圆弧拱、雙曲拱、肋拱、桁架拱、剛架拱等。近年來，各國於諸如[[拱橋|拱橋]]的設計上，除了講究安全實用外，也強調拱軸線優化，連拱計算、拱式建築荷載橫向分佈，使各種形式拱式建築於完善。

拱最早是出現在公元前二千年的[[美索不达米亚|美索不达米亚]]的磚建築<ref>{{cite web|title=Ancient Mesopotamia:Architecture|url=http://oi.uchicago.edu/OI/MUS/ED/TRC/MESO/architecture.html|publisher=The Oriental Institute of the University of Chicago|accessdate=16 May 2012|archive-date=2012-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120516204446/http://oi.uchicago.edu/OI/MUS/ED/TRC/MESO/architecture.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，不過一直到[[古羅馬|古羅馬]]時期才開始有系統的將拱應用在許多建築結構中。

==基本概念==
拱屬於純壓力結構<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pKhbsrIc8IkC&pg=PA32&dq=arch+is+a+pure+compression+form#v=onepage|title=The Engineer's Contribution to Contemporary Architecture|last1=Chilton|first1=John|last2=Isler|first2=Heinz|date=2000|publisher=Thomas Telford|isbn=9780727728784|location=|pages=32|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://oer2go.org/mods/en-boundless/www.boundless.com/physics/textbooks/boundless-physics-textbook/static-equilibrium-elasticity-and-torque-8/applications-of-statics-77/arches-and-domes-314-11286/index.html|title=Arches and Domes|website=oer2go.org|access-date=2019-07-29|archive-date=2019-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729213637/http://oer2go.org/mods/en-boundless/www.boundless.com/physics/textbooks/boundless-physics-textbook/static-equilibrium-elasticity-and-torque-8/applications-of-statics-77/arches-and-domes-314-11286/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FwIkAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA8&dq=arch+is+a+pure+compression+form#v=onepage|title=Shell Structures for Architecture: Form Finding and Optimization|last1=Adriaenssens|first1=Sigrid|last2=Block|first2=Philippe|last3=Veenendaal|first3=Diederik|last4=Williams|first4=Chris|date=2014-03-21|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781317909385|location=|pages=8|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fzuFAFW6YQsC&pg=PA326&dq=arch+is+a+pure+compression+form#v=onepage|title=The Structural Basis of Architecture|last1=Sandaker|first1=Bjørn N.|last2=Eggen|first2=Arne P.|last3=Cruvellier|first3=Mark R.|date=2013-01-11|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781135666873|location=|pages=326|language=en|access-date=2020-09-15|archive-date=2020-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928083936/https://books.google.com/books?id=fzuFAFW6YQsC&pg=PA326&dq=arch+is+a+pure+compression+form#v=onepage|dead-url=no}}</ref>，可以在有大跨度的情形下，將受力轉換為各元件的壓[[應力|應力]]，而不會有張應力。有時會稱為「拱圈作用」（arch action）<ref>{{cite book|last=Vaidyanathan|first=R|title=Structural Analysis, Volume 2|year=2004|publisher=Laxmi Publications|location=USA|isbn=81-7008-584-5|page=127|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=qZPAfoVDtEMC&pg=PA127&dq=arch+action&hl=en&sa=X&ei=jWoMUZOBGKfp0AGn2YHYCw&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAQ|access-date=2013-06-25|archive-date=2016-05-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160528202651/https://books.google.com/books?id=qZPAfoVDtEMC&pg=PA127&dq=arch+action&hl=en&sa=X&ei=jWoMUZOBGKfp0AGn2YHYCw&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAQ|dead-url=no}}</ref>。當拱結構的受力帶到地面時．拱結構會對基地施下一往外的力，稱為「拱推力」。當拱的高度下降時，其往外的拱推力也會變大<ref>{{cite book|last=Ambrose|first=James|title=Building Structures|url=https://archive.org/details/buildingstructur00ambr|year=2012|publisher=John Wiley & Sons, Inc.|location=Hoboken, New Jersey|page=[https://archive.org/details/buildingstructur00ambr/page/n47 30]}}</ref>。為了維持拱圈作用，避免拱結構倒塌，需要抑制往外的拱推力，可能是利用內部的拉桿或是外部的支撐，例如{{link-en|拱臺|abutments}}<ref name="Building Structures">{{cite book|last=Ambrose|first=James|title=Building Structures|url=https://archive.org/details/buildingstructur00ambr|year=2012|publisher=John Wiley & Sons, Inc.|location=Hoboken, New Jersey|isbn=978-0-470-54260-6|page=[https://archive.org/details/buildingstructur00ambr/page/n48 31]}}</ref>。

===固定拱以及鉸接拱===

最常見的幾種真拱為固定拱、兩鉸拱（two-hinged arch）及三鉸拱（three-hinged arch）<ref name="Reynolds's Reinforced Concrete Designer's Handbook, p 41" />。

固定拱最常用在跨度較小的鋼筋混凝土橋以及隧道。固定拱需承受內部結構因為溫度變化產生的[[热胀冷缩|热胀冷缩]]，因此是[[靜不定|靜不定]]結構<ref name="Building Structures"/>。

兩鉸拱（two-hinged arch）最常用在大跨度的橋<ref name="Building Structures" />。這種拱在其拱的底座是由鉸支承固定旳，和固定拱的底座不同，鉸支承可以旋轉<ref>{{cite web|last=Luebkeman|first=Chris H.|title=Support and Connection Types|url=http://web.mit.edu/4.441/1_lectures/1_lecture13/1_lecture13.html|work=MIT.edu Architectonics: The Science of Architecture|publisher=MIT.edu|accessdate=3 February 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121028035620/http://web.mit.edu/4.441/1_lectures/1_lecture13/1_lecture13.html|archivedate=28 October 2012}}</ref>，讓結構可以形變，以配合因為室外溫度變化產生的热胀冷缩。不過仍然會有額外的應力，因此兩鉸拱仍然是靜不定拱，不過情形比固定拱要好很多<ref name="Building Structures" />。

三鉸拱（three-hinged arch）不止在底座有鉸支承固定，在其頂點也有有鉸支承固定。因此可以在水平及垂直的方向變形，以配合因為室外溫度變化產生的热胀冷缩。這種拱沒有因為热胀冷缩產生的應力，因此是靜定結構<ref name="Reynolds's Reinforced Concrete Designer's Handbook, p 41">{{cite book|last=Reynolds|first=Charles E|title=Reynolds's Reinforced Concrete Designer's Handbook|year=2008|publisher=Psychology Press|location=New York|isbn=978-0-419-25820-9 |page=41 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hrOfsy89QxkC&pg=PA41&dq=three-hinged+arch+statically+determinate#v=onepage|via=[[Google_Books|Google Books]]}}</ref>。三鉸拱最常用在中等跨距的拱，例如大型建築的屋頂。三鉸拱的另一個好處是鉸支承底座比固定式底座好施工，可以在中等長度範圍內使用淺的，軸承型基礎。在三鉸拱中，拱的熱热胀冷缩會讓頂點有垂直方向的位移，但二個底座不會有太大的影響，這可以簡化底座的設計<ref name="Building Structures" />。
=== 類型 ===
拱主要可以分為三拱：圓拱、尖拱以及拋物線拱。拱也可以用在[[拱頂|拱頂]]及[[拱廊|拱廊]]上<ref name="Building Structures" />。

圓拱也稱為半圓拱，常用在用重砌體建造的古代拱門<ref name="ambrose32">{{cite book|last=Ambrose|first=James|title=Building Structures|url=https://archive.org/details/buildingstructur00ambr|url-access=limited|year=2012|publisher=John Wiley & Sons, Inc.|location=Hoboken, NJ|isbn=978-0-470-54260-6|page=[https://archive.org/details/buildingstructur00ambr/page/n49 32]}}</ref>。古羅馬建築大量的使用圓拱，而且有很大的跨距。會用許多圓拱接續排列，以形成拱廊，例如[[古羅馬水道|古羅馬水道]]<ref>{{cite book|last=Oleson|first=John|title=The Oxford Handbook of Engineering and Technology in the Classical World|year=2008|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=US|isbn=978-0-19-518731-1|page=299}}</ref>。

尖拱常出現在[[哥特式建筑|哥特式建筑]]中<ref>{{cite book|last=Crossley|first=Paul|title=Gothic Architecture|year=2000|publisher=Yale University Press|location=New Haven, CT|isbn=978-0-300-08799-4|page=58|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LBZ6781vvOwC&printsec=frontcover&dq=gothic+architecture#v=snippet|via=[[Google圖書|Google圖書]]}}</ref>。尖拱相較於圓拱的好處，是尖拱在拱底部產生的橫向推力較小。這可以讓拱的高度提高，也可以有較多安排較密集出入口，這也是哥特式建筑的特點<ref>{{cite book|last=Hadrovic|first=Ahmet|title=Structural Systems in Architecture|year=2009|publisher=On Demand Publishing|isbn=978-1-4392-5944-3|page=289}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=MHHE |title=Structural Systems in Architecture |url=http://dev5.mhhe.com/textflowdev/genhtml/0073379204/13.1.htm |publisher=MHHE.com |accessdate=3 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130313101430/http://dev5.mhhe.com/textflowdev/genhtml/0073379204/13.1.htm |archivedate=13 March 2013 }}</ref>。

{{le|拋物線拱|parabolic arch}}的原理是讓質量平均分佈在拱對地面的投影面上，其內部的壓力會使拱出現[[拋物線|拋物線]]的外形。在主要的拱造形中，拋物線拱產生的橫向推力最大，但其跨距也是最大的。拋物線拱常用在需要大跨距的橋樑中<ref name="ambrose32"/>。

